Deputy Minister of Justice and Correctional Services Thabang Makwetla was found unharmed in the North West after he was hijacked by four gunmen near Life Riverfield Hospital in Johannesburg at around 7:30 pm on Sunday night.Makwetla s spokesperson Ntime Skhosana said the deputy minister was forced into the back seat of his car by the hijackers and drove off. The hijackers stole the cell phone, vehicle and bank cards. They forced him to withdraw money from his bank cards, said Skhosana.However Skhosana couldn t disclose how much was withdrawn from the Makwetla s bank cards. A case has been opened with the Garankuwa police station.